[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] # ADR-001: Dual Database Backend (PostgreSQL + In-Memory)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Decision
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] The app ships with two database backends selectable via `BUG_TRACKER_TEST_DB_BACKEND`:
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - **`postgres`** — PostgreSQL via `pg` driver (production and postgres-specific tests)
[CLAUDE] - **`memory`** — in-process in-memory store (default for unit tests)
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Rationale
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] Running PostgreSQL for every unit test requires Docker and adds significant test startup time. An in-memory backend allows the fast test suite (`npm run test`) to run without any infrastructure.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **Why:** Fast feedback loops during development. The in-memory backend provides sub-second test startup vs. waiting for Docker PostgreSQL to be ready.
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] **How to apply:** Default all unit tests to `memory` backend. Only use `npm run test:unit:postgres` when the change is specifically testing database-level behaviour (schema constraints, SQL queries, migrations).
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Trade-offs
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] | | In-Memory | PostgreSQL |
[CLAUDE] |---|---|---|
[CLAUDE] | Speed | Very fast | Slower (network + process) |
[CLAUDE] | Fidelity | May miss SQL-specific behaviour | Matches production exactly |
[CLAUDE] | Infrastructure | None | Docker required |
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] ## Implementation
[CLAUDE] 
[CLAUDE] - `src/lib/db/database-client.ts` — abstraction interface
[CLAUDE] - `src/lib/db/local-test-database.ts` — in-memory implementation
[CLAUDE] - `src/lib/db/postgres-client.ts` — PostgreSQL implementation
[CLAUDE] - `src/lib/db/test-database.ts` — selects backend based on env var
[CLAUDE] === END FILE ===
[CLAUDE] 
